e anatomy sequence because water or edema is less\nconspicuous and anatomy is usually clearly delineated.\n▪ T2 is known as the pathologic sequence because the high signal (white) occurring\nwhen there is edema is very easy to see.\n▪ A good example is effusion in the knee joint. The fluid in the joint is very obvious\nas white or bright signal on T2-weighted images.\n▪ Today, there are many variations in MRI imaging sequences, and more are being\ndiscovered all the time. These sequences can be used to suppress signal from fat\nor from free fluid.\n7"}